# Kubernetes CNI (RKE2 / Canal)

This directory is used by kubelet when RKE2 is deployed on the node.
Canal installs `10-canal.conflist` and related files here at runtime.

Podman CNI configs must not live in this directory — they are under
`/etc/cni/podman/net.d/` (see `/etc/containers/containers.conf.d/99-podman-cni-dir.conf`).

Nodes without RKE2 keep this directory empty.
